## 🧑‍💻 Overview

This project involved the migration of a **legacy email system for approximately 2000 users** within the KwaZulu-Natal government (COGTA KZN), transitioning from:

- Novell GroupWise  
- POP3-based email clients  

➡ to  
- Microsoft Exchange Server (On-Premises)

This was a **large-scale enterprise email migration only** (no SharePoint, Teams, OneDrive, or Active Directory changes).

The objective was to modernize messaging infrastructure, centralize mail services, and improve reliability and administrative control in a constrained government ICT environment.

---

## 🎯 Objectives

- Migrate ±2000 users to Microsoft Exchange Server  
- Eliminate GroupWise and POP3 dependencies  
- Standardize Outlook-based email access  
- Improve email reliability and uptime  
- Centralize email hosting and management  
- Reduce legacy system complexity  
- Improve IT support efficiency  

---

## 🏗️ Legacy Environment Challenges

- Novell GroupWise email system  
- POP3-based mail retrieval  
- No centralized mailbox governance  
- Client-side email storage (PST/local files)  
- High administrative overhead  
- Inconsistent mail delivery experience  

### ⚠️ Government Infrastructure Constraints
- No strict control over minimum hardware specifications  
- Large number of client machines operating below recommended Exchange/Outlook requirements  
- Performance limitations on older desktops and laptops  
- Infrastructure inconsistencies across departments  

---

## 🚗 Field Deployment & Travel Requirements

This was not a centralized data center migration only — it required **extensive onsite deployment across multiple government facilities**.

Teams were required to travel and perform migrations at:

- Natalia Building (PMB)  
- Wadley House (PMB)  
- Mayville (Durban)  
- Stanger offices  

Each site required:
- Manual mailbox migration validation  
- Onsite Outlook reconfiguration  
- User support and troubleshooting  
- Hardware and performance checks on legacy systems  

This added significant logistical complexity and coordination effort across regions.

---

## 🧱 Target Architecture

- Microsoft Exchange Server (On-Premises)  
- Outlook (MAPI) email client standardization  
- SMTP-based mail routing  
- DNS configuration (MX, A, Autodiscover)  
- Centralized mailbox storage on Exchange  

---

## 🔧 Migration Approach

### 1. Environment Assessment
- Audited ~2000 mailboxes  
- Identified POP3 configurations  
- Analysed mailbox sizes and user distribution  
- Planned phased migration batches across regions and sites  

---

### 2. Exchange Deployment
- Installed Microsoft Exchange Server  
- Configured mailbox databases  
- Defined mail routing policies  
- Set up SMTP services  

---

### 3. Mailbox Migration
- Extracted data from GroupWise environment  
- Converted legacy mailbox formats  
- Migrated users in controlled phased batches  
- Validated data integrity post-migration  

---

### 4. End-User Transition
- Reconfigured Outlook profiles to Exchange  
- Removed GroupWise client dependency  
- Standardized email access across organization  
- Provided onsite and remote user support during cutover  

---

## 🔐 Security Improvements

- Removal of POP3 authentication methods  
